.TH "BREW\-MAN" "1" "April 2026" "Homebrew"
.SH NAME
brew\-man \- Display a man page bundled with an installed formula
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBbrew\fP \fBman\fP [\fIoptions\fP] \fIformula\fP [\fImanpage\fP] \fBman\fP (\fB\-\-list\fP|\fB\-\-interactive\fP) \fImanpage\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Display a man page bundled with an installed formula\.
.P
Homebrew kegs (especially keg\-only formulae) are not on the default \fBMANPATH\fP, so \fBman\fP does not reliably find their pages\. When multiple providers ship the same page name, \fBman\fP silently returns the first match\. This command resolves man pages \fBby formula\fP and makes ambiguity explicit\.
.P
By default, \fBbrew man <formula>\fP resolves man pages within the specified formula only\. The optional \fImanpage\fP argument defaults to the formula name\. With \fB\-\-html\fP, renders the man page via \fBmandoc \-T html\fP and opens it in a browser (respecting \fBHOMEBREW_BROWSER\fP or \fBBROWSER\fP)\.
.P
Use \fB\-\-list\fP or \fB\-\-interactive\fP to search across system and other Homebrew formulae\. With \fB\-\-list\fP, shows all locations where a given man page is found (both system paths and Homebrew formula kegs)\.
.P
With \fB\-\-interactive\fP, presents a numbered list with origin labels to interactively select which copy of a man page to view\.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
\fB\-d\fP, \fB\-\-debug\fP
Display any debugging information\.
.TP
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
Make some output more quiet\.
.TP
\fB\-v\fP, \fB\-\-verbose\fP
Make some output more verbose\.
.TP
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
Show this message\.
.TP
\fB\-H\fP, \fB\-\-html\fP
Render the man page as HTML and open it in a browser (respects \fBHOMEBREW_BROWSER\fP or \fBBROWSER\fP)\.
.TP
\fB\-l\fP, \fB\-\-list\fP
List all locations where the named man page is found\.
.TP
\fB\-i\fP, \fB\-\-interactive\fP
Interactively resolve ambiguity when multiple copies of a man page are found\.
